fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.views

Interface IListFetchFilter

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @PluginService
 @FunctionalInterface
public interface IListFetchFilter
    Extension point to enable customization of list fetching behavior. For example, this enables a component to specify additional fetchable cells that may be required to compute a value or a label (in addition to those directly required for display).

    Instances of this filter are made available to the IDataViewService via the OSGi service registry. Filters are selected in order of priority, starting with the highest service.ranking property first, followed by the service.id property. All registered filters will be queried.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Method Detail

      • beforeDataListFetch

        IListView beforeDataListFetch(IListView listView)
        Optionally provides a customized list view instance that replaces the specified instance. This is invoked immediately prior to invocation of the toList method.

        Note: when returning a customized implementation, you do not need to implement the toList method (it will be invoked on the default implementation, using the attributes of any returned customized implementation). When providing a customized implementation, customize only the attributes you need, and implement all other interface methods such that they delegate to the instance provided as a parameter to this method.

        Parameters:
        listView - the non-null list view instance. Note that the supplied instance may have already been filtered by a higher-priority filter.
        Returns:
        a customized (filtered) instance, if the filter needs to modify any attributes, or null if the filter does not need to perform any customization (irrelevant view or context...).
        Since:
        1.0
